From ea2af6ee4a409a54ac8ba2ace2aeb0e3d338635f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Sun, 19 Apr 2026 21:19:09 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 5/5] feat: aceternity-inspired premium animation components
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Four new Aceternity-UI-inspired interactions, reimplemented from
scratch using our existing stack (framer-motion, Tailwind v4). No
external packages installed.

Components
- SpotlightCard: per-card cursor-follow radial gradient. Tracks
  mousemove on the card element, writes rgba(212,165,116,0.22)
  radial overlay at the cursor position, animates opacity on
  enter/leave. Used to wrap every phase card on the home page.
- BackgroundBeams: 6 diagonal SVG paths with animated pathLength
  and fade opacity, staggered delays, amber stroke gradient.
  Sits behind HeroVisual; intentionally low opacity so it
  complements the iris rings rather than competing.
- TextGenerate: word-by-word blur→sharp stagger (filter: blur(10px)
  → blur(0)). Splits on whitespace (not per-letter, which looks
  jittery at display sizes). Accessibility-first: sr-only mirror
  of the full text + aria-hidden on the animated spans.
- Bento grid layout for "How it works": 3-tile grid with hero
  tile (col-span-2 row-span-2), tall sidebar tile (row-span-2),
  wide banner tile (col-span-3). Distinct backgrounds per tile:
  cream-radial, dark-amber-glow, amber-wash. Oversized numerals
  per tile, animated waveform bars in the dark tile, decorative
  spotlight-stage SVG in the banner tile.

All four respect prefers-reduced-motion (via MotionConfig plus
explicit useReducedMotion fallbacks where animate props are
conditional). All decorative elements aria-hidden. Amber on dark
passes WCAG AA; amber-on-light uses --cnib-yellow-on-light (#6B4F2A)
for body text contrast.
